# Conway’s Game of Life – Advanced Simulator & Pattern Ecosystem

A fully interactive Conway’s Game of Life engine featuring real-time simulation, custom rule editing, RLE import/export, and a built-in pattern creation tool.

---

## 🧠 Overview

This project is a complete Game of Life ecosystem made of two tools:

### 🧬 Simulator (`gol.html`)
A high-performance cellular automaton engine with advanced visualization and control features.

### 🧩 Pattern Builder (`goladder.html`)
A visual editor for creating, saving, and exporting custom Game of Life patterns.

### 📦 Pattern Library (`patterns.js`)
A simple registry of RLE-based patterns used by the simulator.

---

## 🚀 Simulator Features (`gol.html`)

### Simulation Engine
- Conway’s Game of Life (customizable rules)
- Rule editor (B/S format UI)
- Efficient Set-based grid system
- Cell aging system

### Visualization Modes
- Grid toggle
- Heatmap mode (age-based coloring)
- Cell color mode
- Ghost trail rendering
- Full-cell rendering mode

### Analysis Tools
- Population graph
- Peak / low / average tracking
- Growth slope calculation
- Stability detection (variance-based)

### Navigation & View
- Zoom in/out (mouse wheel)
- Pan (drag / shift-drag constraints)
- Minimap with click-to-jump
- Reset view option

### Pattern System
- Built-in patterns from `patterns.js`
- RLE import (paste or URL)
- Pattern rotation (0°, 90°, 180°, 270°)
- Pattern ghost preview

### Chaos Mode
- Random cell generation with density control

---

## 🎮 Controls

### Simulation
- `Space` → Play / Pause
- `Step` → Advance one generation
- `Ctrl + Z` → Undo
- `Ctrl + Y` → Redo

### Editing
- Left click → Draw
- Right click → Pan
- Mouse wheel → Zoom
- `[ / ]` → Brush size

### Modes
- `E` → Toggle erase mode
- `F` → Full cell mode
- `G` → Toggle grid
- `C` → Cycle colors / heatmap
- `T` → Toggle ghost mode
- `R` → Toggle rules panel
- `H` → Hide UI

### Pattern Tools
- `V` → Rotate pattern
- `P` → Toggle ghost preview

---

## 🧩 Pattern Builder (`goladder.html`)

A dedicated tool for designing patterns visually.

### Features
- Click-to-draw grid editor
- Erase mode
- Undo / redo system
- RLE import
- Pattern metadata:
  - codename (internal key)
  - viewname (display name)
  - hovername (tooltip)
- Pattern list manager
- Export system:
  - HTML dropdown format
  - JavaScript object format

---

## 📦 Pattern System (`patterns.js`)

Example structure:

```js
window.PATTERN_DATA = {
  glider: "bo$2bo$3o!",
  blinker: "3o!",
  switchengine: "2o$2o2$3bo$3bo$4b3o!"
};
